verbose_text: RNA binding protein RNPC1 has been shown to play suppressive roles in various tumors, such as RNPC1 as a suppresser of metastasis and epithelial-mesenchymal transition (EMT) of breast cancer via directly binding to HOXD10 and CDH5 mRNAs and thus resulting in the activation of STARD13 correlated competitive endogenous RNA (ceRNA) relationship [XREF_BIBR] and inducing the sensitivity of HER-2-positive breast cancer cells to trastuzumab through upregulating HER2 [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: binding to HOXD10 and CDH5 mRNAs and thus resulting in the activation of STARD13
